{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/astronomykit\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AstronomyKit provides a type-safe Swift interface for astronomical calculations. This article walks you through installation and your first calculations."}]},{"anchor":"Installation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Installation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add AstronomyKit to your Swift package:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/heirloomlogic\/AstronomyKit.git\", from: \"0.1.0\")","]"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or in Xcode: "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"File → Add Package Dependencies"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" and enter the repository URL."}]},{"anchor":"Your-First-Calculations","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Your First Calculations"},{"anchor":"Import-the-Package","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Import the Package"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import AstronomyKit"]},{"anchor":"Set-Up-Your-Observer-Location","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Set Up Your Observer Location"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most astronomical calculations require an observer location on Earth:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ New York City","let observer = Observer(latitude: 40.7128, longitude: -74.0060)","","\/\/ With elevation (in meters)","let denver = Observer(latitude: 39.7392, longitude: -104.9903, height: 1609)"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Get-the-Current-Time","type":"heading","text":"Get the Current Time"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"AstronomyKit uses ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/AstroTime","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for all time-based calculations:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Current time","let now = AstroTime.now","","\/\/ From a specific date","let newYear = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1, hour: 12)","","\/\/ From Foundation Date","let fromDate = AstroTime(Date())"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Calculate-a-Position","type":"heading","text":"Calculate a Position"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Find where a celestial body appears in your sky:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Mars in the local sky","let mars = try CelestialBody.mars.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","print(\"Altitude: \\(mars.altitude)°\")     \/\/ Height above horizon","print(\"Direction: \\(mars.compassDirection)\")  \/\/ N, NE, E, etc."]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Find-the-Moon-Phase","type":"heading","text":"Find the Moon Phase"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","print(\"\\(Moon.emoji(for: angle)) \\(Moon.phaseName(for: angle))\")","\/\/ Output: 🌔 Waxing Gibbous"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Get-Rise-and-Set-Times","type":"heading","text":"Get Rise and Set Times"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["if let sunrise = try CelestialBody.sun.riseTime(after: .now, from: observer) {","    print(\"Sunrise: \\(sunrise.date)\")","}","","if let sunset = try CelestialBody.sun.setTime(after: .now, from: observer) {","    print(\"Sunset: \\(sunset.date)\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Error Handling","anchor":"Error-Handling"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All potentially failing calculations throw ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/AstronomyError","type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["do {","    let position = try CelestialBody.earth.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","} catch AstronomyError.earthNotAllowed {","    print(\"Cannot observe Earth from Earth!\")","} catch {","    print(\"Calculation failed: \\(error)\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Next Steps","anchor":"Next-Steps"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/TimeAndObservers","type":"reference"},{"text":" — Deep dive into time and location handling","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialPositions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Calculate positions for any celestial body"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonPhases","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — Explore moon phase calculations"}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/TimeAndObservers"],"title":"Essentials","anchor":"Essentials"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Getting Started with AstronomyKit"},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to add AstronomyKit to your project and perform basic astronomical calculations.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://AstronomyKit/documentation/AstronomyKit":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit","url":"\/documentation\/astronomykit","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"AstronomyKit","abstract":[{"text":"Swift bindings for Don Cr